This paper deals with optimization problems on dynamic flow networks, which are typically studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of sink location is a classic problem in network engineering and optimization, which falls under the category of network economics (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the concept of robust optimization, which is a topic in game theory and decision making (cs.GT). The use of trees as a special case for the problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes a polynomial time solution, which involves algorithmic techniques and optimization, making it relevant to the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
